# Synthetica MVP & Live Scraping Walkthrough

> [!TIP]
> The application now features a fully automated web extraction layer alongside the original semantic layouts. You can view the new Settings dashboard at `/settings` and hit the **Trigger Live Scrape** button on the home dashboard to pull real-time data instead of mock data!

## Phase 1 Highlights (The Foundation)
- Initialized a modern Next.js (App Router) codebase.
- Engineered a premium, custom glassmorphism aesthetic natively configured in pure CSS to eliminate the heavy reliance on rigid frameworks.
- Implemented and fully integrated three Polymorphic Views: **NYT Deep Read**, **Insta-Scroll Card**, and **TikTok Velocity**.

## Phase 2 Highlights (Live Configuration & Extraction)

### The Settings & Configuration Engine
- We have introduced a centralized configuration matrix where you can curate specific target constraints across four vectors:
  - **Semantic Topics** (e.g. tracking "AI")
  - **Exact Sites** (e.g. blog endpoints)
  - **Content Creators** (e.g. specialized X handles)
  - **Communities** (e.g. Subreddits)
- You can navigate directly into `/settings` and observe a clean, dark-mode table view presenting your configured ingestion matrix and prioritization weights.

### The Stealth Extraction Engine
- Implemented `lib/scraper/engine.ts` utilizing `playwright-extra` and `puppeteer-extra-plugin-stealth`.
- Designed the backend to seamlessly toggle between **a Local Stealth headless instance** OR **CDP connection to KikiLogin / AdsPower** if intense WAFs require manual session farming!
- **Reddit Ingestion**: Created an initial extraction logic `platforms/reddit.ts` tailored exactly for Reddit nodes, successfully parsing Titles, Authors, and DOM textbodies without tripping bot protection.

### Main Dashboard Real-time Trigger
- We placed an asynchronous fetch trigger on the main dashboard (`/page.tsx`). Clicking **"Trigger Live Scrape"** automatically fires up the backend Playwright process invisibly, pulls the latest 5 posts from the Community configuration, formats them contextually via the AI pipeline models, and instantly pushes them into the top of the "Raw Feed Inbox".

